4.

library(caret)
library(xgboost)

#  integer 
Train_Y_tmp = as.integer(Train_Y)-1 
Test_Y_tmp = as.integer(Test_Y)-1

nfold = 4 #  fold 
set.seed(1001)
folds = createFolds(factor(Train_Y_tmp), k = nfold, list = FALSE)

dev_result =  rep(0, nrow(Train_X)) #  valid 
pred_te = rep(0, nrow(Test_X)) #  test 
#  for  valid
for (this.round in 1:nfold){      
  valid = c(1:length(Train_Y_tmp)) [folds == this.round] # valid index
  dev = c(1:length(Train_Y_tmp)) [folds != this.round] # train index
  
  dtrain= xgb.DMatrix(data= as.matrix(Train_X[dev,]), 
                       label= Train_Y_tmp[dev])
  dvalid = xgb.DMatrix(data= as.matrix(Train_X[valid,]) , 
                        label= Train_Y_tmp[valid])
  
  # 
  param = list(objective = "binary:logistic", 
               eval_metric = "auc",
               max_depth = 10,
               eta = 0.01,
               gamma = 0,
               subsample = 0.8,   
               colsample_bytree = 0.8,
               min_child_weight = 8,  
               colsample_bylevel = 0.8,
               lambda = 1, 
               alpha = 0,
               booster = "gbtree",
               silent = 0
  ) 
  
  # 
  model =  xgb.train(data = dtrain,
                    params= param, 
                    nrounds = 5000, 
                    verbose = T, 
                    list(val1=dtrain , val2 = dvalid) ,      
                    early_stopping_rounds = 50 , 
                    print_every_n = 10,
                    maximize = T
  )
  
  #  fold  model 
  saveRDS(model, file = paste0("./Model/xgb_",this.round,".rda"))
  pred = predict(model,as.matrix(Train_X[valid,]))
  dev_result[valid] = pred  
  pred_test  = predict(model,as.matrix(Test_X))
  pred_te = pred_te +pred_test
}

library(pROC)
pred_test = pred_te/nfold
auc(Test_Y_tmp,pred_test)
## Area under the curve: 0.9015
  • threshold threshold Y N
threshold <- function(predict, response) {
  r <- pROC::roc(response, predict)
  r$thresholds[which.max(r$sensitivities + r$specificities)]
}

#  test_threshold
train_threshold = threshold(dev_result,Train_Y_tmp)
test_threshold = threshold(pred_test,Test_Y_tmp)
cat("valid threshold",train_threshold,"; testdata threshold",test_threshold)
